<subSubSection id="C300E5EEFFA6FFA1A69E8C2F1CFDFB67" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA5B665FFA6FFA1A69E8C2F1CFDFB67" blockId="2.[151,1436,982,1188]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B96E6A77FFA6FFA1A69E8C2F1930FB94" bold="true" box="[198,257,1085,1111]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<materialsCitation id="3B72BC38FFA6FFA1A77C8C2F1CF5FB67" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3128191305" collectionCode="E, G" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
Since the species was described in honour of 
<collectionCode id="ED0B2EA0FFA6FFA1A56E8C2F1B7AFB94" box="[822,843,1085,1111]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15670" name="Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" type="Herbarium">E</collectionCode>
. Hassler, we opted to choose the material collected by him as the 
<typeStatus id="54A108C7FFA6FFA1A7618C761995FBBD" box="[313,420,1124,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">lectotype</typeStatus>
of this name. In addition, there is some question about the second 
<typeStatus id="54A108C7FFA6FFA1A2F58C761D3DFBBD" box="[1197,1292,1124,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">syntype</typeStatus>
: it was cited as 
<emphasis id="B96E6A77FFA6FFA1A6EE8C991961FB67" box="[182,336,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
Fiebrig 
<quantity id="4CE21B80FFA6FFA1A74E8C991961FB67" box="[278,336,1163,1188]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.56616" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" unit="in" value="1404.0">1404</quantity>
</emphasis>
in the protologue, but the specimen at 
<collectionCode id="ED0B2EA0FFA6FFA1A5418C981B1FFB67" box="[793,814,1162,1188]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
is clearly labelled as 
<emphasis id="B96E6A77FFA6FFA1A2738C991CF5FB67" box="[1067,1220,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Fiebrig 1484</emphasis>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
